oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Proceedings of the Twentieth Annual Conference (1987). Bovine "Give Away" and Awards
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bovine Practitioners, American Association of
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The AABP again sponsored a "Bovine Give-Away" in the form of ten $50.00 prizes. The drawing was made by AABP President, Dr. George Washington and the event was organized by Dr. Samuel Hutchins 3rd, Exhibits Manager in collaboration with the exhibitors. Dr. Robert L. Darlington, Pilchuck Veterinary Hospital, Snohomish, Washington was named the 1987 Outstanding Bovine Practitioner of the Year at the Annual Membership Luncheon Meeting on Friday, November 13. AABP awards for excellence in preventive veterinary medicine, sponsored by MSD-AGVET division of Merck & Co., Inc., were announced during the annual business meeting on Friday, November 13.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1987; vi, xii-xiv
